The paper deals with joint transceiver design in wireless sensor networks, which involves optimization of linear filters and beamformers. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the mean square error (MSE) criterion, which is commonly used in control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of multiple antennae and linear filters suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
